Definition.WordDefinition: Second-rate \Sec"ond-rate`\, a. Of the second size, rank, quality, or value; as, a second-rate ship; second-rate cloth; a second-rate champion. --Dryden. [1913 Webster]
second-rate adj : moderate to inferior in quality; "they improved the quality from mediocre to above average"; "he would make a poor spy" [syn: {mediocre}, {poor}]
